<paragraph id="535A100FC1F39902E7A8AE0D26124D5E" pageId="0" pageNumber="4421">Occurs as terrestrial in lowland rain forest.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3767C1EFFAAC6246D76D3FA38FD68ECD" pageId="0" pageNumber="4421" type="taxon discussion">
<paragraph id="E32F3DDAD8F76D9B46D77CA8CF518CFD" pageId="0" pageNumber="4421">Taxon discussion</paragraph>
<paragraph id="75052EA5043F596E2BAC886DA2277B3C" pageId="0" pageNumber="4421">
This species is easily recognizable by the 2 - 5 pairs of pinnae, cuneate at base, and tubular yellow to orange glands on the receptacle (
<bibRefCitation id="3C916DBB4062070F874B8E7A7B815054" author="Smith, A. R." editor="Harling, G." journalOrPublisher="University of Goeteborg, Stockholm" pageId="0" pageNumber="4421" title="Flora of Ecuador" year="1983">Smith 1983</bibRefCitation>
). The presence of these glands is shared with 
<taxonomicName id="73E5697D38C043DA467AF5C8D888F032" authority="" authorityName="" class="Centricae" family="Chironomidae" genus="T." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="T. (Meniscium) andreana" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="4421" phylum="Diatomeae" rank="species" species="andreana" subGenus="Meniscium">T. (Meniscium) andreana</taxonomicName>
(Sodiro) C.V.Morton, the closest species to 
<taxonomicName id="888E659BBB331C9438C97E9EA3DC3F7D" authority="" authorityName="" class="Centricae" family="Chironomidae" genus="T." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="T. (Meniscium) arcana" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="4421" phylum="Diatomeae" rank="species" species="arcana" subGenus="Meniscium">T. (Meniscium) arcana</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="2610BDABBC37FAABAA8F13E8A93B187F" author="Smith, A. R." editor="Harling, G." journalOrPublisher="University of Goeteborg, Stockholm" pageId="0" pageNumber="4421" title="Flora of Ecuador" year="1983">Smith 1983</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
